gomodel:SYNGO_2047  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: TARP γ-8 is a multipass transmembrane protein which is concentrated in the postsynaptic density plasma membrane at four types of Schaffer collateral/commissural (SSC) synapses in the adult mouse hippocampus: perforated and non-perforated synapses on pyramidal cells; axodendritic synapses on parvalbumin-positive (PV) and PV-negative interneurons (Figure 5C, D, J). Among the TARPs examined in this paper (γ-2, γ-3, γ-8), TARP γ-8 was the only TARP found at nonperforated synapses.\n\nAntibodies used in this paper were validated by immunofluorescence labeling (Figure 7) and electron microscopy (Table 2-3) using KO mice for the corresponding TARP.\n\n6/12/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Animals.\nWe used male C57BL/6 wild-type (WT) mice and knock-out (KO) mice defective in GluA1, GluA2, GluA3, or GluA4 (Yamasaki et al., 2011) and in TARP γ-2 (Yamazaki et al., 2010), TARP γ-3, or TARP γ-8 (Fukaya et al., 2006) at the adult stage (2-4 months of age). TARP γ-3-KO mice were produced using the C57BL/6N ES cell line RENKA (Mishina and Sakimura, 2007), as reported previously (Fukaya et al., 2006; Yamazaki et al., 2010). All animal experiments were performed in accordance with the guidelines laid down by the animal welfare committees of Hokkaido University. The numbers of mice examined for respective experiments were as follows: in situ hybridization (WT, 6); immunofluorescence (WT, 9; TARP γ-2-KO, 3; TARP γ-3-KO, 3; TARP γ-8-KO, 3); quantitative postembedding immunogold and conventional electron microscopy (WT, 3; TARP γ-2-KO, 3; TARP γ-3-KO, 3; TARP γ-8-KO, 3)." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2047" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

